SIMPLE: perspicuous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Perspicuous
<hw>Per*spic"u*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>perspicuus</ets>, from <ets>perspicere</ets> to look through. See
<er>Perspective</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Capable of being through;
transparent; translucent; not opaque.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Peacham.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Clear to the understanding; capable of being clearly
understood; clear in thought or in expression; not obscure or ambiguous;
<as>as, a <ex>perspicuous</ex> writer; <ex>perspicuous</ex>
statements.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧The purpose is
<xex>perspicuous</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Per*spic"u*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Per*spic"u*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perspirability</ent>⟦br⟧
